definitions.definition: Either of two species of bird of the genus Pyrrhocorax in the crow family Corvidae that breed mainly in high mountains and on coastal sea cliffs of Eurasia .
The white-winged chough , of genus Corcorax in the Australian mud-nest builders family, Corcoracidae , that inhabits dry woodlands .
